      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE PREACHER (4) comes here fresh from a second in a Listed feature won by Munny The Munster nine days ago over 2270m at Riverina Paceway. Class act who will be hard to beat. QUEEN KIZEN NZ (3) was out of the money two back at Maryborough. Turned in a better run last time out when third over 2150m at Bendigo, beaten 10 metres. Meeting a deeper field this time but she has the ability to mix it with them. MAESTRO (7) failed to fire two runs ago then broke and finished fifth last start over 2645m at Globe Derby Park, coming home 25 metres from the winner. It doesn't get any easier but he is talented enough to be competitive. TWEEDLEDEE NZ (6) is better than his last-start seventh over 2240m at Melton and deserves another chance.",
